Create the Databases needed for the Project 6

The below Steps will be performed in SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)

The Name of the Databases to create are:

RecSta

RecSta_Stg

RecSta_DW



 

Follow the below Steps to create the above 3 Databases and refer the motion screen below for more.

  1.  On SSMS window, right click on ‘Databases’, then click on ‘New Database…’.
  2.  .Give a Descriptive Database Name like ‘RecSta’.
  3. Click ‘Ok’ to create the Database.
  4. Repeat Steps 1 to 3 for - RecSta_Stg (Staging) and  RecSta_DW (Data Warehouse) databases,
  5. Refresh the Databases folder to see if the Databases are created.


[Motion Screen]


How to create a Database

https://www.sqlservertutorial.net/sql-server-basics/sql-server-create-database/
